FBIS4-61269 "drsov087_s_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 Georgia Situation in Abkhazia's Gali District Remains Tense Situation in Abkhazia's Gali District Remains Tense LD0405131694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1251 GMT 4 May 94 LD0405131694 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchegoleva] [Text] Sochi 4 May TASS -- The situation in the Gali district of Abkhazia remains tense. Georgian subversive groups continue acts of terrorism against the civilians. Georgian troops are concentrating on the line of confrontation along the Inguri River, the Abkhazian Defence Ministry said on Wednesday. Georgian units acting in the Kodor gorge continue shelling adjacent villages. As a result of artillery shelling of the village of Lata last night, two Abkhazian soldiers were wounded, the Abkhazian Ministry of Information and the press said.
